        {
            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "The [reasoning for 0.179](https://github.com/sharkdp/pastel/blob/5e9f9c01fe167f59ecc0888975c7ddc095816ca2/src/lib.rs#L728-L732) makes sense (and their calculations are correct, of course).\n\nAs a note, 'mini.hipatterns' (which was partially used as a reference for `vim.lspdocument_color`) uses OKLab lightness with 0.5 threshold to decide the contrast color. The difference might be visible to using the plain relative luminance, but probably less so after changing the current threshold to 0.179.",
